  "content": {
    "intro": "Everyone says to \"support\" your child's math learning. But what does that actually mean? Here's a practical breakdown.",
    "sections": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "level": 2,
        "text": "What \"Accompanying\" Is NOT"
      },
      {
        "type": "list",
        "items": [
          "Being a math tutor",
          "Doing homework for them",
          "Hovering over every problem",
          "Getting emotionally invested in every mistake",
          "Sacrificing your sanity for their grades"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "level": 2,
        "text": "What \"Accompanying\" Actually Is"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "level": 3,
        "text": "1. Creating the Conditions"
      },
      {
        "type": "list",
        "items": [
          "Quiet space for practice",
          "Consistent time in the schedule",
          "Functional tools (app, materials)",
          "Freedom from distractions"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "level": 3,
        "text": "2. Providing Emotional Support"
      },
      {
        "type": "list",
        "items": [
          "Celebrating effort, not just results",
          "Normalizing mistakes",
          "Staying calm when they're frustrated",
          "Showing belief in their ability"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "level": 3,
        "text": "3. Enforcing the Routine"
      },
      {
        "type": "list",
        "items": [
          "Making practice non-negotiable (gently but firmly)",
          "Protecting practice time from interruptions",
          "Following through consistently"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "level": 3,
        "text": "4. Monitoring Progress (Lightly)"
      },
      {
        "type": "list",
        "items": [
          "Checking dashboard weekly, not daily",
          "Noticing patterns (stuck? advancing? struggling?)",
          "Adjusting resources if needed"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "callout",
        "style": "tip",
        "text": "Think of yourself as a coach, not a player. You create the conditions, encourage, and adjust strategy – but they do the work."
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "level": 2,
        "text": "The Accompanying Mindset"
      },
      {
        "type": "table",
        "headers": [
          "Instead of",
          "Think"
        ],
        "rows": [
          [
            "\"I need to teach them\"",
            "\"The tools teach; I support\""
          ],
          [
            "\"Their grades reflect on me\"",
            "\"Their journey is their own\""
          ],
          [
            "\"I must fix every mistake\"",
            "\"Mistakes are learning\""
          ],
          [
            "\"More practice = more progress\"",
            "\"Consistent practice = progress\""
          ],
          [
            "\"I should know all the answers\"",
            "\"We can figure it out together\""
          ]
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "level": 2,
        "text": "What This Looks Like Daily"
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "text": "A good day of \"accompanying\":"
      },
      {
        "type": "list",
        "items": [
          "\"Hey, it's math time.\" (You announce)",
          "[They practice for 10-15 minutes, you're available nearby]",
          "\"How'd it go?\" (You ask casually)",
          "\"Nice! See you tomorrow.\" (You move on)"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "text": "That's it. No drama. No teaching. No stress."
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "level": 2,
        "text": "When to Do More"
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "text": "Sometimes accompanying means stepping in more:"
      },
      {
        "type": "list",
        "items": [
          "When they're genuinely stuck (not just frustrated)",
          "When the tool isn't working (too hard, too easy)",
          "When emotional issues are blocking learning",
          "When you notice concerning patterns"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "text": "But these are exceptions, not the daily norm."
      }
    ],
    "faq": [
      {
        "question": "Isn't this too hands-off?",
        "answer": "It might feel that way, but research shows parental over-involvement can increase anxiety and reduce intrinsic motivation. This approach builds independence."
      },
      {
        "question": "What if my child has genuine learning struggles?",
        "answer": "More support may be needed – possibly professional tutoring or evaluation. But the general framework still applies: you support, experts teach."
      },
      {
        "question": "How do I know if I'm doing enough?",
        "answer": "If they're practicing consistently and making some progress over months, you're doing enough. You don't have to see daily improvement."
      }
    ],
